 Drain on a rack and sprinkle with seeds as desired, while boiling remaining bagels."},{"content":"Return bagels to baking tray and bake for 8 minutes (260°C). Reduce oven temperature to 230°C then bake for a further 6-8 minutes until nicely browned. Allow to cool on a wire rack."},{"content":"Serve with spreads, cream cheese or other fillings of choice."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Canadian hard wheat flour is best for making bagels.","Adding bicarbonate of soda to the water alkalises it, which helps to produce a better crust.","If you do not want to cook the bagels immediately, refrigerate bagels after step 4 for up to 48 hours.","Cooked bagels can be frozen for up to a month.","Ingredients can be doubled to make 12 bagels.","Bagels are unusual in that they are boiled before baking and they also must have a very stiff dough - much stiffer than any other bread. This produces the typical chewy character with a good crust. The advantage of this method is that the bagels can be prepared ahead and cooked as required."],"basicInfo":["medium","15m","1h 20m","6 portions"]}